flowRoot.flowPara: Lock screen appears to slides down, over the session.
Icons in the bottom right indicate when smart card or fingerprint authentication is available.

User selection is shown after boot or after selecting sign in as another user (the back button would only be shown in the latter case). After selecting a user, the lock/login screen is shown, with the password entry revealed.
This version of the user selection screen is only shown when there's between two and eight users.
If there's more than eight users, or its a networked environment, a different version of the user selection screen is shown.

text.tspan: Sign in as a different user...

flowRoot.flowPara: If not listed is selected, image grid is replaced by user name entry:
Typing replaces the clock with the password entry. FIXME: how to activate the password entry with a pointing device or touchscreen?
When the password has been correctly entered, the screen slides up out of the way.
